4 SECTION 11. SPECIAL LANGUAGE. NOT TO BE INCORPORATED INTO THE ARKANSAS
5 CODE NOR PUBLISHED SEPARATELY AS SPECIAL, LOCAL AND TEMPORARY LAW.
6 TRANSFER AUTHORITY. The Secretary of the Department of Human Services shall
7 have transfer authority provided by the following:
8 (a) DEPARTMENT OF HUMAN SERVICES RENOVATION FUND. The Secretary of the
9 Department of Human Services is authorized to request fund transfers
10 according to the provisions established by Arkansas Code Ann. 19-5-1020,
11 Department of Human Services Renovation Fund, as amended herein; and
12 (b) MATCH TRANSFER. The Secretary of the Department of Human Services,
13 with the approval of the Chief Fiscal Officer of the State, is authorized to
14 effect inter-agency and inter-divisional fund transfers for the purpose of
15 providing the State's matching share for payments made to that Division or
16 Office or its service providers for services eligible for federal
17 reimbursement under programs administered by the Department of Human
18 Services. The Department of Human Services shall report to the Legislative
19 Council or Joint Budget Committee on a quarterly basis all fund transfers
20 made in accordance with the authority granted by this section; and
21 (c) REALLOCATION OF RESOURCES: (1) The Department of Human Services (DHS)
22 provides hundreds of different services to over 1 million Arkansans. The
23 specific mix of service needs and the funding and staffing required to
24 provide them can vary significantly based on many factors, including natural
25 disasters, changing federal mandates and funding sources, demographic shifts,
26 fluctuating court-ordered services, social trends, and job market variations
27 such as nursing shortages. The impact of these factors through the course of
28 any fiscal year make it very difficult for the Department to accurately
29 predict the exact needs for funding, appropriation and positions in each of
30 its over 100 different appropriations. To ensure that it can respond quickly
31 to changing client needs and make the most effective use of the resources
32 allocated to it, the Department of Human Services shall be authorized to
33 utilize the reallocation of resource authority to make the proper adjustments
34 to the budgets within the Department. Therefore, upon determination by the
35 Secretary of the Department of Human Services that a reallocation of
36 resources within the department is necessary for the efficient and effective
11 04-10-2025 16:54:28 LCW012

As Engrossed: H3/12/25 H4/10/25 HB1105
1 operation of the department, the Secretary, with approval of the Governor,
2 shall have the authority to request, from the Chief Fiscal Officer of the
3 State, a transfer of positions, appropriations, line item appropriations, and
4 funds within or between existing and newly created divisions, offices,
5 sections, or units of the department. Provided, however, that no transfer of
6 funds or appropriation that provides direct support or matching support for
7 the Arkansas Medicaid Program shall be made to any other fund account or
8 appropriation that does not directly support the Arkansas Medicaid Program.
9 Further, no positions, funds, or appropriation authorized during the budget
10 process for the Division of Children and Family Services' compliance with
11 initiatives established under the Angela R. consent decree shall be
12 transferred to any other division. Nothing in this provision is intended to
13 prevent the one-time transfers of savings in any other program to the
14 Arkansas Medicaid Program, with the exception of the provisions previously
15 cited for the Division of Children and Family Services – Angela R. consent
16 decree. The Division of Developmental Disabilities – Grants to Community
17 Providers line item of the Developmental Disabilities Services - Grants-in-
18 Aid appropriation may not be decreased. The appropriation, funding, and
19 positions provided for the five Human Development Centers shall remain at a
20 level sufficient to ensure quality care for the Centers' residents. The
21 exemptions provided in this subsection whereby certain DHS Programs and
22 Divisions are protected from appropriation, fund, or position transfers are
23 applicable only to the reallocation or transfer authority granted herein, and
24 not by any reductions which are applicable to all state programs.
25 The Secretary of the Department of Human Services shall submit any
26 requests for transfers to and must receive approval of the requests for
27 transfers from the Chief Fiscal Officer of the State, the Governor, and the
28 Arkansas Legislative Council or Joint Budget Committee prior to the effective
29 date of the transfers. Provided, however, that the Department of Human
30 Services shall be limited to submitting no more than four reallocation of
31 resources transfer requests during any fiscal year. In each Departmental
32 request no single division will request reallocation for more than one
33 purpose as listed in this section. Transfer authority for unforeseen purposes
34 shall further be limited to no more than 5% of the total appropriation,
35 funding, and positions authorized for the Department. Reallocation of
36 resources transfers may include multiple items but shall be limited to the
12 04-10-2025 16:54:28 LCW012

As Engrossed: H3/12/25 H4/10/25 HB1105
1 following purposes:
2 i) Medicaid Program;
3 ii) Facilities and institutions costs, including operational expenses and
4 construction/renovation/equipping expenses;
5 iii) Departmental grants and contracts;
6 iv) Court ordered settlements and payments;
7 v) Payment of administrative expenses, including but not limited to, overtime
8 and other costs of personnel for critical services or functions necessary to
9 carry out the mission of the agency;
10 vi) Restructuring efforts as deemed necessary to comply with new and/or
11 unanticipated federal or state mandates; and/or
12 vii) Redirecting internal resources, both direct and/or indirect, to meet
13 client needs and services.
14 Determining the maximum number of employees and the maximum amount of
15 appropriation and general revenue funding for a state agency each fiscal year
16 is the prerogative of the General Assembly. This is usually accomplished by
17 delineating such maximums in the appropriation act(s) for a state agency and
18 the general revenue allocations authorized for each fund and fund account by
19 amendment to the Revenue Stabilization law. Further, the General Assembly has
20 determined that the Department of Human Services may operate more efficiently
21 if some flexibility is provided to the Department of Human Services
22 authorizing broad powers under the Reallocation of Resources provisions
23 herein. Therefore, it is both necessary and appropriate that the General
24 Assembly maintain oversight by requiring prior approval of the Legislative
25 Council or Joint Budget Committee as provided by this section. The
26 requirement of approval by the Legislative Council or Joint Budget Committee
27 is not a severable part of this section. If the requirement of approval by
28 the Legislative Council or Joint Budget Committee is ruled unconstitutional
29 by a court of competent jurisdiction, this entire section is void.
30 (2) If it is determined that the requested reallocation of resources
31 transfers should be made, the Chief Fiscal Officer of the State shall then
32 initiate the necessary transfer documents to reflect the transfers upon the
33 fiscal records of the Treasurer of State, the Auditor of State, the Chief
34 Fiscal Officer of the State, and the Department of Human Services. In
35 addition, the Chief Fiscal Officer of the State, together with the Co-
36 Chairpersons of the Legislative Council or Joint Budget Committee, may
