18 SECTION 13. SPECIAL LANGUAGE. NOT TO BE INCORPORATED INTO THE ARKANSAS
19 CODE NOR PUBLISHED SEPARATELY AS SPECIAL, LOCAL, AND TEMPORARY LAW.
20 DEPARTMENT OF HUMAN SERVICES COMPREHENSIVE AGENCY REVIEW. The Arkansas
21 Legislative Council - Hospital and Medicaid Study Subcommittee shall perform
22 a comprehensive review of the Department of Human Services, which shall
23 commence at the direction of the co-chairs of the Arkansas Legislative
24 Council, in consultation with the subcommittee co-chairs. This review shall
25 include, but is not limited to: administrative policies and functions,
26 personnel and staffing evaluations, and revenues and expenditures of the
27 department, divisions, and providers. The subcommittee shall prioritize the
28 review as follows: the Shared Services division, the Division of Children and
29 Family Services, and the Division of County Operations, with further
30 prioritization of divisions to be determined by the subcommittee. The review
31 shall include input and recommendations from the Attorney General's Medicaid
32 Fraud Unit and the Department of Inspector General's office.
33 The preliminary recommendations and report shall be completed within
34 six months of the subcommittee‘s initial meeting. Upon completion of this
35 preliminary report, the subcommittee shall provide the department, the
36 Governor, and the Arkansas Legislative Council with a report to include
15 04-10-2025 16:54:28 LCW012

As Engrossed: H3/12/25 H4/10/25 HB1105
1 recommendations and desired metrics with expected timelines of completion to
2 meet the desired outcomes provided in the preliminary report. At the
3 direction of the chair of the Arkansas Legislative Council - Hospital and
4 Medicaid Study Subcommittee, the subcommittee may add recommendations and
5 approve and review actions by the department in accordance with the
6 preliminary recommendations.
7 The final report and outcomes, including recommending legislation to
8 address findings, shall be presented at the final Arkansas Legislative
9 Council meeting of the 95th General Assembly.
10 The Department of Human Services shall report to the subcommittee
11 monthly the status of implementation of the recommendations with review and
12 approval of all steps taken to meet the metrics and desired outcomes of the
13 department in accordance with the recommendations by the subcommittee and by
14 the Arkansas Legislative Council.
15 The provisions of this section shall be in effect only from July 1,
16 2025 through June 30, 2026.
17
18 SECTION 14. COMPLIANCE WITH OTHER LAWS. Disbursement of funds
19 authorized by this act shall be limited to the appropriation for such agency
20 and funds made available by law for the support of such appropriations; and
21 the restrictions of the State Procurement Law, the General Accounting and
22 Budgetary Procedures Law, the Revenue Stabilization Law, the Regular Salary
23 Procedures and Restrictions Act, or their successors, and other fiscal
24 control laws of this State, where applicable, and regulations promulgated by
25 the Department of Finance and Administration, as authorized by law, shall be
26 strictly complied with in disbursement of said funds.
27
28 SECTION 15. LEGISLATIVE INTENT. It is the intent of the General
29 Assembly that any funds disbursed under the authority of the appropriations
30 contained in this act shall be in compliance with the stated reasons for
31 which this act was adopted, as evidenced by the Agency Requests, Executive
32 Recommendations and Legislative Recommendations contained in the budget
33 manuals prepared by the Department of Finance and Administration, letters, or
34 summarized oral testimony in the official minutes of the Arkansas Legislative
35 Council or Joint Budget Committee which relate to its passage and adoption.
